quote.p:
—The proposed six-city program is not a “stable” objective;
                                presumably once a deployment decision is announced it would not be
                                politically feasible to deny Zeus defenses to other major population
                                centers, and we would be committed to proceed with at least a
                                29-city, 70-battery program as recommended by NORAD and the Army, at a cost of
                                about 15 billion dollars;
